Package org.svvrl.goal.cmd

Interface Summary
CommandExtension A CommandExtension is used to extend the command pool.
Expression An Expression provides an interface of expressions in GOAL scripts.
GameSolverInterface This interface defines a command-line plugin for game solvers.
Statement A statement is a block of expressions containing control flows.
 

Class Summary
AbstractCommandExtension This class provides a default implementation of CommandExpression.
AbstractExpression This class provides a default implementation of Expression.
AccExtension This extension provides maximization and minimization of Büchi acceptance conditions of finite state automata.
AlphabetExtension This class provides an extension that offers a command for manipulating the alphabet of an automaton.
AperiodicExtension This extension provides a command for testing the aperiodicity of an automaton or the language of an automaton.
BatchExtension A batch extension provides a command for executing GOAL scripts.
BigStepSolverInterface This interface provides a command-line interface for the big step solver.
BinaryExpr A BinaryExpr object represents a binary expression.
BlockStmt A block statement contains a sequence of statements.
BreakStmt A break statement can break a for-loop or a while-loop.
ClassicalBuchiSolverInterface This interface provides a command-line interface for the classical Büchi game solver.
ClassicComplementExtension A ClassicComplementExtension provides a command for complementing a classic finite state automaton.
ClassificationExtension This class provides classification of an automaton or a QPTL formula based on the temporal hierarchy.
CloneExtension This extension provides a command that can make a clone of an object.
CloseExtension A close extension provides a command for closing a GOAL window by its window ID.
CmdHandler A CmdHandler provides an implementation of ConsoleHandler.
CmdPlugin CmdPlugin initializes the command-line plugin.
CmdUtil CmdUtil provides utility methods for the command-line package.
CommandExpression A CommandExpression is an expression formed by a command name and arguments for the command.
CommandRepository CommandRepository provides methods for accessing the command pool.
ComplementCommand A ComplementCommand is a command expression for a complementation construction.
ComplementExtension A ComplementExtension provides a command for complementing an automaton by a complementation construction.
ConcatenationExtension This class provides a command for concatenating two automata.
Constant A constant is an object that can be evaluated without the context.
ContainmentExtension A ContainmentExtension provides a command for checking if the language of an automaton is contained in the language of another automaton.
Context A Context object is a map from a variable name to its value.
ContinueStmt A ContinueStmt can continue a for-loop or a while-loop.
ConvertExtension A convert extension provides a command for converting an automaton to another type of automaton, a regular expression, or an ω-regular expression.
DeterministicComplementExtension A DeterministicComplementExtension provides a command for complementing a deterministic automaton.
DeterministicExtension A deterministic extension provides a command for testing if an automaton is syntactically deterministic.
DeterminizationExtension A determinization extension provides a command for determinizing a nondeterministic automaton into an equivalent deterministic automaton.
DominionDecompositionSolverInterface This interface provides a command-line interface for the DominionDecomposition solver.
EchoExtension An echo extension provides a command for printing an object as a string.
EmptinessExtension An emptiness extension provides a command for testing if the language of an automaton is empty or not.
EquivalenceExtension An equivalence extension provides a command for testing if two automata accept the same language.
ExitStmt An exit statement quits the GOAL process.
ForStmt A for-loop statement binds an element in a set of objects to a lvalue in one iteration and executes its body statement iteratively for every binding.
GenerateExtension A GenerateExtension provides a command for generating automata and QPTL formulae randomly.
GlobalOptimizationSolverInterface This interface provides a command-line interface for the generic solver with global optimizations.
HelpStmt A help statement displays the help message of a command or all commands.
HomomorphismExtension This class provides a command extension for checking if the first automaton is homomorphic to the second automaton.
IfStmt An if-statement contains a set of guarded branches.
InputTestExtension A InputTestExtension provides a command for testing if a word is accepted by an automaton.
InteractiveStmt An InteractiveStmt starts the interactive mode.
IntersectionExtension An IntersectionExtension provides a command for taking the intersection of two automata.
IsomorphismExtension This class provides a command extension for checking if two automata are isomorphic.
KurshanComplementExtension A KurshanComplementExtension provides a command for complementing a DBW by the Kurshan's construction.
LayoutExtension A layout extension provides a command for laying out the active automaton in a GOAL window by the default layout algorithm.
LoadExtension A LoadExtension provides a command for loading a file.
Lval A Lval object represents an l-value.
McNaughtonZielonkaSolverInterface This interface provides a command-line interface for the McNaughton-Zielonka solver.
MinimizationExtension A MinimizationExtension provides a command for minimizing classic automata.
MinusMinus This class provides expressions of the form --$x or $x-- where $x is an l-value.
ModifiedSafraComplementExtension A ModifiedSafraComplementExtension provides a command for complementing an NBW by the modified Safra's construction.
MullerSchuppComplementExtension A MullerSchuppComplementExtension provides a command for complementing an NBW by the Muller-Schupp construction.
MultiSetStmt A MultiSetStmt assigns values to variables simultaneously.
NamesExtension A NamesExtension provides a command for printing names of some extensions, such as codecs, layout algorithms, etc.
NullExpr A NullExpr is evaluated to null always.
OmegaExtension This class provides a command extension for taking the ω operation on a classic finite state automaton.
OpenExtension An OpenExtension provides a command for opening a file as an editable object in a GOAL window.
ParityExtension This class provides a command for operations on parity conditions.
PastExtension A PastExtension provides a command for testing if a QPTL formula contains any past operator.
PitermanComplementExtension A PitermanComplementExtension provides a command for complementing an NBW by the Safra-Piterman construction.
PlusPlus This class provides expressions of the form ++$x or $x++ where $x is an l-value.
PreferenceExtension A PreferenceExtension provides a command for getting user preferences or changing user preferences at runtime.
ProductExtension An ProductExtension provides a command for taking the product of two finite state automata or taking the product of a game and a finite state automaton.
PromelaExtension A PromelaExtension provides a command for outputting the Promela code of an NBW.
PropertyExtension A PropertyExtension provides a command for getting or setting properties of an editable object.
QPTLExtension This class provides an extension for QPTL formulae.
RamseyComplementExtension A RamseyComplementExtension provides a command for complementing an NBW by the Ramsey-based construction.
RankComplementExtension A RankComplementExtension provides a command for complementing an NBW by the Rank-based construction.
ReachabilitySolverInterface This interface provides a command-line interface for the Reachability solver.
ReadlineExtension A ReadlineExtension provide a command for reading a file line by line.
RecursiveSolverInterface This interface provides a command-line interface for the Recursive solver.
ReduceExtension A ReduceExtension provides a command for reducing the unreachable and dead states from an automaton.
RepositoryExtension This class provides a command extension for accessing the repositories.
ReverseExtension A ReverseExtension provides a command for reversing a classic finite state automaton.
SafraComplementExtension A SafraComplementExtension provides a command for complementing an NBW by the Safra's construction.
SatisfiabilityExtension A SatisfiabilityExtension provides a command for testing the satisfiability of a QPTL formula.
SaveExtension A SaveExtension provides a command for saving an object to a file.
SeparationExtension This class provides an extension of past/future separation.
SeqExtension A SeqExtension provides a command for generating a sequence of numbers.
SetStmt A SetStmt assigns a value to an l-value.
ShellExpr A ShellExpr is an expression that can invoke a shell command.
SimplifyExtension A SimplifyExtension provides a command for simplifying an automaton or a formula by various techniques.
SimulatedExtension This class provides a command for testing if an automaton is simulated by another automaton.
SimulationEquivalenceExtension A SimulationEquivalenceExtension provides a command for testing if two automata are simulation equivalent.
SleepExtension A SleepExtension provides a command for idling for a specified time period.
SliceComplementExtension A SliceComplementExtension provides a command for complementing an NBW by the Slice-based construction.
SmallProgressMeasureSolverInterface This interface provides a command-line interface for the small progress measure solver.
SolveExtension This extension provides a command for solving games.
SplitExtension A SplitExtension provides a command for splitting an object into a set of elements.
StatExtension A StatExtension provides a command for outputting the statistical data of an automaton or a QPTL formula.
TestExtension This class is for internal usage.
TimeExpr A TimeExpr returns the current time.
TranslateExtension A TranslateExtension provides a command for translating a QPTL formula to an equivalent automaton.
TryStmt This class provides try statements:
UnaryExpr A UnaryExpr object represents a unary expression.
UnionExtension A UnionExtension provides a command for taking the union of two compatible automata.
ValidityExtension A ValidityExtension provides a command for testing the validity of a QPTL formula.
WAAComplementExtension A WAAComplementExtension provides a command for complementing an NBW by the complementation construction via weak alternating automata.
WAPAComplementExtension A WAPAComplementExtension provides a command for complementing an NBW by the complementation construction via weak alternating parity automata.
WhileStmt A WhileStmt represents a while-loop statement.
 

Enum Summary
BinaryOp This enumeration lists the binary operations.
DeterminizationAlgorithm This enumeration lists available determinization algorithms.
UnaryOp This enumeration lists the unary operators.
 

Exception Summary
BreakException A BreakException is thrown by a BreakStmt initially can should be handled by ForStmt and WhileStmt.
ContinueException A ContinueException is thrown by a ContinueStmt initially can should be handled by ForStmt and WhileStmt.
EvaluationException An evaluation exception is thrown if there is a problem in evaluating a command-line statement or expression.
